laboratory_examinations.findings: An abnormally mucosally-enhancing 10 mm in diameter appendix with associated periappendiceal stranding, findings overall compatible with appendicitis. Cholelithiasis without secondary signs of cholecystitis. A 2.2 x 3.3 cm predominantly hypoattenuating liver lesion with peripheral nodular enhancement, most compatible with a benign hemangioma. No other focal liver lesions identified.
